txt.en: While observing Parphád, you note several texts exposed to the elements, threatened by the invaders or being carried off by the invaders themselves. Ascbert would want these texts protected and may even wish to read them himself.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>Warning: This quest requires Parphád: Order of Magnitude to be underway in order to access Parphád. If that quest has been completed, or failed, you will be unable to exit and re-enter Parphád in order to complete this quest.</rgb>

While observing Parphád, you note several texts exposed to the elements, threatened by the invaders or being carried off by the invaders themselves. Ascbert would want these texts protected and may even wish to read them himself.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>Warning: This quest requires Parphád: Order of Magnitude to be underway in order to access Parphád. If that quest has been completed, or failed, you will be unable to exit and re-enter Parphád in order to complete this quest.</rgb>
'While I would have preferred these texts to remain within Parphád, I understand they were under risk of damage. You've done well to bring them to me.'
Pieces of weathered parchment may be found in Parphád.\n\nYou should collect pieces of weathered parchment and bring them to Ascbert.
'Are there any other texts at risk such as these? We must preserve them if we are able.'
